[More information on these cases would be appreciated. While not confirmed
there was some information that the suspected case mentioned in British
Columbia did have a travel history that included Hong Kong prior to the
onset of illness. There have now been suspected cases of an acute
respiratory syndrome with an associated "atypical pneumonia" reported from
China (Hong Kong, Guangdong), VietNam, Singapore, Taiwan and now
Canada. We await more information on the studies currently underway
investigating the etiology of these clusters as well as more information on
the epidemiologic studies currently underway. - Mod.MPP]
